Description: Mercurial as a Subversion client
DescDetail: <<
	hgsubversion is an extension for Mercurial that allows using Mercurial
	as a Subversion client.
<<
DescUsage: <<
	Add the two lines
	hgext.rebase =
	hgsubversion =
	to the [extensions] section of your ~/.hgrc file to enable.
	Use hg help hgsubversion to check that it is installed correctly and
	get usage information.
	
	%n defaults to using subvertpy-py%type_pkg[python] to interface with svn.
	subvertpy-py%type_pkg[python] currently only works with svn 1.6. If you
	want to use %n with svn 1.7, install svn-swig-py%type_pkg[python]
	and export HGSUBVERSION_BINDINGS=swig in your shell environment.
<<
